{
  "name": "shear",
  "description": "Reference-parity matrix for soft-shear = linear-falloff Move (xfrm.shear preset). Each case freezes before/after vertex pairs captured from the reference engine and replays the xfrm.shear preset in vibe3d WITHOUT any external engine at runtime; vibe3d reproduces every case bit-for-bit. Coverage: all three translate axes (TX/TY/TZ) each crossed with a perpendicular linear gradient (Y, Z, X), plus negative sign, double magnitude, and gradient reversal. Built on an empty-reset scene so the welded segmented cube is the ONLY geometry (a plain reset's default cube would survive prim.cube's append and be sheared too). Capture must zero all of TX/TY/TZ per case \u2014 the tool attrs persist across cases otherwise.",
  "source": "Frozen reference capture (xfrm.shear, linear falloff, parameter matrix; capture via tools/local/modo_diff/probe_shear.py).",
  "tolerance": 0.0001,
